article.headline: Lipscomb 77, Kennesaw 48
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Eddie Ard scored 20 points to go with five rebounds, two assists and a block in leading Lipscomb to a 77-48 win over Kennesaw State on Sunday afternoon to win the Atlantic Sun Conference regular season championship. James Poindexter added 11 points for the Bisons (19-9, 15-5) who jumped out to a fast lead over the Owls (12-17, 10-10) and built on it throughout the game. Lipscomb led by 23 at the half, 42-19. Trey Williams handed out a game-high eight assists for Lipscomb. Eleven players scored for the Bisons, who shot 45.6 percent from the field for the game. Kennesaw State shot just 29.2 percent. Dusty Moore led the Owls with 12 points, followed by Golden Ingle's 11. The Atlantic Sun Conference tournament starts Thursday at East Tennessee State in Johnson City, Tenn., where top-seed Lipscomb will meet No. 8 seed Mercer in the opener.
